725154f-a.text:
27th Avenue, north side, between Sth and 9th Streets, showing the Joseph Blackwell house of 1873. Joseph Blackwell was a drygoods merchant in New York City. The house is set back about 150 feet from the normal builiing line. Subsequent
to 1929 it was used as a aultiple dwelling.
View 1:  Eugene L.Armbruater  1922
View 2:  P.L. Sperr  March 11, 1931
View 3:  George D. Chian  April 27, 1940
